Routing in Azure VNets determines how network traffic flows between resources.

Azure provides:

* System routes (default)
* User-defined routes (custom)
* BGP routes (for hybrid connectivity)

For example, traffic can be routed through a firewall for inspection.

A real-life use case is directing all outbound traffic through a security appliance.

Another example is optimizing traffic flow between subnets for performance.

Routing ensures efficient and secure data flow.
